  "text": "Nei's genetic distance estimates the sharing of molecular phenotypes; complete sharing is indicated by a score of zero, while no sharing is reflected by infinite values of genetic distance [CITATION_1] . The estimates of genetic distance (D N ) observed here did not exceed the threshold of 0.015 (Table 2) , indicating a low level of genetic distance between samples upstream and downstream of the dam. Other studies found genetic distance values higher than here and considered these values to indicate low levels of genetic differentiation. Populations of Astyanax altiparanae studied by [CITATION_2] gave genetic distance estimates close to 0.12 in an area without geographical barriers; [CITATION_3] found higher levels of genetic distance (approximately 0.61) for Astyanax scabripinnis.",
